Prerequisites:
1) Install Java
2) Install IntelliJ
	- Maven project
	- Select Java openjdk

In lesson:
1) Install Selenium / cucumber / junit
    - Add to pom.xml:
            <dependencies>
                <dependency>
                    <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
                    <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
                    <version>4.5.0</version>
                </dependency>
                <dependency>
                    <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
                    <artifactId>cucumber-java</artifactId>
                    <version>7.8.0</version>
                </dependency>
                <dependency>
                    <groupId>junit</groupId>
                    <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
                    <version>4.13.2</version>
                    <scope>test</scope>
                </dependency>
                <dependency>
                    <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
                    <artifactId>cucumber-junit</artifactId>
                    <version>7.8.0</version>
                    <scope>test</scope>
                </dependency>
            </dependencies>
2) Initial folder structure
    - src/test/
        + resources (Maven source directories: resources)
    - src/test/resources
        + drivers
        + features
3) Google "chrome driver"
4) Click link "https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads"
5) CLick latest -> download "chromedriver_win32.zip"
6) Extract "chromedriver.exe" to src/test/resources/drivers
